model.name: Tang2019 - Pharmacology modelling of AURKB and ZAK interaction in TNBC

notes.body: Aurora Kinase B and ZAK interaction modelEquivalent of the stochastic model used in "Network pharmacology model predicts combined Aurora B and ZAK inhibition in MDA-MB-231 breast cancer cells" by Tang et. al. 2018. The only difference is cell division and partitioning of the components, which are available in the original model for SGNS2.
